{"TopicId":133691,"ForumId":69,"TopicTitle":"Going into IVA switches control point (even when point is not a command part)","CreatedByName":"allmhuran","CreatedById":66124,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-07T17:08:05Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"allmhuran","CreatedById":66124,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-07T17:08:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis one\u0027s been around pretty much forever. I\u0027ve had problems because of it recently so I\u0027m posting it up again.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf you set the control point for a vessel and then go into the IVA view of a different part, the control point of the vessel switches to that second part. Thsi happens \u003Cem\u003Eeven if that second part is not a command part.\u00A0\u003C/em\u003EIt shouldn\u0027t happen at all, not even for command parts.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autoSizeIframe\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fgfycat.com%2FHandyHonorableFinwhale\u0026amp;key=HandyHonorableFinwhale\u0022 style=\u0022height:549px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-07T17:08:59Z\u0022 title=\u002203/07/2016 05:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 7, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by allmhuran\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Mister Dilsby","CreatedById":232743,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-07T19:13:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes. One must be very careful with this effect. I make a comic on the forum, and often need to take shots from different positions and locations in the ship to tell the story the way I want. Sometimes I forget about this, and I set prograde or retro hold for a burn\u00A0while I jump through different IVA views to get reaction shots of the crew. Hilarity ensues \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo, not sure you\u0027re really asking a \u0027question\u0027 here. Looks more like a PSA, and a very useful and well-done video of one \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KSP Bro AE","CreatedById":154259,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-07T21:33:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\ncompletely natural. I actually use it to my advantage\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"allmhuran","CreatedById":66124,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-08T02:42:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNathanKell posted info a nice hidden treat that should\u00A0fixe\u00A0this behaviour on the KSP subreddit. There\u0027s no GUI setting for this so it would have to be set by editing the file directly. I\u0027m not sure whether this also fixes it for non-command pods, I will check tonight.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:2px -2px;padding:0px;color:rgb(85,85,85);font-size:11px;letter-spacing:normal;font-family:sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(250,250,250);\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca rel=\u0022external\u0022 style=\u0022text-decoration:none;color:rgb(136,136,136);margin-right:3px;padding:1px;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003E[\u2013]\u003C/a\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.reddit.com/user/NathanKell\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022 style=\u0022text-decoration:none;color:#800080;margin-right:.5em;font-weight:bold;\u0022\u003ENathanKell\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022margin-right:.5em;padding-top:0px;padding-right:2px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;color:rgb(85,85,85);border:0px;vertical-align:middle;text-indent:25px;width:auto;height:22px;background-image:url(\u0026quot;//b.thumbs.redditmedia.com/lCtKOQEP_hKz-Mh3TYXw4hWAk1rPSYUwyzkjZlzeBDA.png\u0026quot;);background-attachment:scroll;background-color:transparent;background-position:0px -1267px;background-repeat:no-repeat;\u0022 title=\u0022RSS Dev\u0022\u003ERSS Dev\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:11px;\u0022\u003E12 points\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E3 hours ago\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:small;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv style=\u0022margin:5px 0px;padding:0px;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-weight:400;font-size:14px;line-height:1.4;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:0px;padding:0px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.42857em;\u0022\u003E\nThe switch of control point when going IVA\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cstrong style=\u0022font-style:inherit;font-weight:600;margin:0px;\u0022\u003Ecan be turned off in settings.cfg\u003C/strong\u003E. Change IVA_RESETS_CONTROL_POINT from True to False.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022margin:.357143em 0px 0px;padding:0px;font-size:14px;line-height:1.42857em;\u0022\u003E\nI added that in 1.0.5.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-03-08T02:51:05Z\u0022 title=\u002203/08/2016 02:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 8, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by allmhuran\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-08T03:13:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis rapidly scuttles any launch involving crew facing any other direction\u00A0with SAS\u00A0locked prograde. Thank you \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022http://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002275006\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/75006-nathankell/\u0022\u003E@NathanKell\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0for the config file setting.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NathanKell","CreatedById":75006,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-03-08T03:52:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt disables any reference transform shift on entering IVA. So it should stop that ever happening.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}